CC0 1.0 Universal — Public Domain Dedication

Everything this project itself creates in this repository is dedicated to the
public domain — both the CODE (the browser music engines, dev-time tools,
scripts, and any original shared libraries written for the project) and the
PROSE (the wiki under `wiki/` and the text of the public project site under
`docs/`). One dedication now covers the whole project; there is no separate
license for code versus prose.

To the extent possible under law, the authors and maintainers of this project
(Tom Gally, and Claude, Anthropic's AI, which does the writing and the
engineering) have waived all copyright and related and neighboring rights to
this work worldwide under the CC0 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication. You
may copy, modify, distribute, and perform the work — code and prose alike, for
any purpose, commercial or not — all without asking permission.

The work is provided "as is", without warranties of any kind.

The immutable reference material under `previous-experiments/` is the prior
work of the project owner and is included for reference only.

